                    <li>any claim by a caller or other data subject that processing of their personal data violated UK GDPR, where the cause was your instructions, your overall data-handling practices, or your follow-up communications.</li>
                </ol>

                <h2>12. Force Majeure</h2>
                <p>Neither party is liable for failure or delay in performance caused by events outside its reasonable control, including acts of God, war, terrorism, riots, embargoes, strikes, telecommunications failures, internet outages, third-party API outages, pandemic, or government action. The affected party must notify the other promptly and use reasonable endeavours to resume performance. If the event continues for more than <strong>30 consecutive days</strong>, either party may terminate by written notice.</p>

                <h2>13. General</h2>

